 Milimiani location Chief Sylvester Momanyi was arrested by Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission (EACC) officials for allegedly demanding Sh100,000 bribe from a widow to help her secure a letter of administration to property. ALSO READ:

Awaiting Uhuru next big move EACC detectives apprehended the administrator moments after receiving the treated money from the widow on Thursday. He is in custody in Kitale Police Station awaiting to be arraigned in court. Trans-Nzoia County Commander Samson ole Kine said: “The chief had allegedly demanded the money from the woman to help her secure a latter of administration for the property left behind by her husband but instead she alerted EACC who laid a trapped and arrested him,” said Mr Kine. In May, anti-graft officials arrested a policeman for allegedly imposing illegal levies on farmers whose livestock strayed to a farm.  Avoid becoming a victim of Fake News. Subscribe to the Standard Group SMS service by texting 'NEWS' to 22840.